[2025-07-20 17:32:05] [INFO] my_app_logger: Retrieved documents: {'documents': [Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='Moaaz Siddiqui\nGulshan Iqbal, Karachi\n♂phone0318-2553857 /envel⌢pemoaaz7151@gmail.com /linkedinlinkedin.com/in /githubgithub.com/moaaz12-web\nSummary\nA software engineering graduate with a strong foundation in AI, NLP, CV, and Python development. My journey\nhas included hands-on experience with large language models (LLMs), AI-powered solutions, and seamless backend\nintegrations.\nEducation\nNED University of Engineering and Technology Oct. 2020 – July 2024\nBachelor of Science in Software Engineering - GPA: 3.50 Karachi, Sindh\nExperience\nGaditek December 2024 – Present\nAssociate Software Engineer - AI Karachi, Pakistan\n• Worked on AI-based backend tools for interview preparation, candidate CV customization, and job description\ngeneration for recruiters using FastAPI\n• Researched and implemented an agentic Langgraph-based workflow that takes user query and automatically performs all\nactions like a human.'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='and an API endpoint.\n• Applied AWS Textract for OCR on receipt data, fine-tuned LayoutlmV3 on the OCR results using Amazon SageMaker,\nand deployed the model on HuggingFace inference API.\nProjects\nAdvanced RAG application| Python, LangChain, HuggingFac, Streamlit Code\n• Built a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) application with Langchain for document question answering.\n• Utilized advanced RAG techniques like multi-query retriever, reranking, and semantic chunking for improved\nperformance\n• Leveraged transformer models for llm and text embeddings, and Streamlit for creating an interface\nAutomatic Number Plate recognition| Python, YOLOv8, OpenCV, Tkinter, EasyOCR Code | Demo\n• Created a Tkinter application for tracking cars in real time and their license plates.\n• Used pretrained YOLOv8 model for car detection and fine-tuned YOLOv8 model for license plate detection\n• Leveraged SORT tracker for real-time car tracking and EasyOCR for extracting license plate text.'), Document(metadata={'version': 'unknown', 'text': None, 'effective_date': '2025-07-19', 'source': 'moaaz resume.pdf', 'page': 0.0, 'doc_id': 'moaaz resume'}, page_content='generation for recruiters using FastAPI\n• Researched and implemented an agentic Langgraph-based workflow that takes user query and automatically performs all\nactions like a human.\n• Created a recommendation algorithm for recruiters, where they can post a job description and get recommended\ncandidates for that job description\nDevelopers World LLC March 2023 – Jume 2024\nAI Engineer Remote, USA\n• Fine-tuned Mistral LLM using supervised fine tuning (SFT) for rating question answer pairs. Manually crafted the\ndataset by myself.\n• Developed a multilingual AI pipeline with ChatGPT API, OpenAI Whisper, and Roberta for multilingual QA, with web\nsearch and summarization\n• Fine-tuned and deployed transformer models on Amazon SageMaker for hate speech detection, utilizing secure S3 storage\nand an API endpoint.\n• Applied AWS Textract for OCR on receipt data, fine-tuned LayoutlmV3 on the OCR results using Amazon SageMaker,\nand deployed the model on HuggingFace inference API.\nProjects')]}
